g.text: actions are a way to wrap some code and keep the app light.
They can also dispatch events, either with the default
responder right back to the app,
or hack something together and do custom stuff.
The custom responder is a super hacky channel.
Chats map 1-1 with a session. Configures what agents
will run, what tools can be used, etc.
Configuration is generally done via the config
Each agent has access to following:
- Agent Environment (git branch, start ref, etc)
